    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="181"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hart</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of America</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-11-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 119.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your telegram of November 1, which I translate as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Proceed with demand Star and Herald claim. This Government imperatively
                            insists on prompt payment.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hill.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Owing to the disturbed condition of affairs, as reported in my No. 120 of this
                    date, it has not been practicable to do business with the Government. I expect
                    to have an interview with the minister for foreign affairs this afternoon, when
                    of course the matter will be brought to a head and the Department will be at
                    once advised by cable.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chas. Burdett Hart</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
